Create a &quot;pointer&quot; to the start of the array, just an int initialized to 0.&lt;br&gt;
Now you have two possible cases, either the number you&#39;re currently pointing at is equal to the next one, in which case it&#39;s duplicated, or it&#39;s not and you can skip it.&lt;br&gt;
If it&#39;s not equal skip it, otherwise create a new temporary pointer and loop until it reaches a number that is different than the one pointed at by the original pointer, or you reached the end of the array.&lt;br&gt;
